  "prompt": "Why do American writers use yellow paper?",
  "response": "American writers sometimes use yellow paper, specifically yellow legal pads, for a few reasons:\n\n1. **Contrast and Readability**: The yellow color is believed to offer better contrast than white paper, making it easier on the eyes during long writing or editing sessions.\n\n2. **Psychological Effect**: Some people feel that yellow is a stimulating color that can boost creativity and concentration.\n\n3. **Tradition and Availability**: Yellow legal pads have been a staple in American office supplies for decades. Their association with professionalism and legal or professional work might contribute to their popularity among writers.\n\n4. **Organization**: Yellow paper is easily distinguishable from standard white paper, which can help in organizing notes and manuscripts.\n\nThese factors contribute to the continued use and popularity of yellow paper among American writers and professionals.",
